A 0.1 ml aliquot of the same supernatant used for superoxide dismutase enzyme activity determination was used to assay for thioredoxin peroxidase (TPx) activity. thioredoxin peroxidase (TPx) decomposes H2O2 in the presence of a reducing agent, and we detemermined thioredoxin peroxidase (TPx) enzyme activity by measuring the rate of decrease in absorbance at 240 nm and subtracting the catalase (CAT) enzyme activity. The formulas used to calculate thioredoxin peroxidase (TPx) activity are as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
